# Splitting Dataset
set.seed(123)
index <- sample(seq_len(nrow(df)), size = floor(0.5 * nrow(df)))
train <- df[index, ]
test <- df[-index, ]

actual <- test$diabetes  # Define actual once here and use it consistently

## Logistic Regression Model
logistic <- glm(diabetes ~ ., data = train, family = "binomial")

# Confusion Matrix
confusion_matrix_plot <- function(cm, model_name = "Model") {
  df_cm <- as.data.frame(as.table(cm))
  
  ggplot(df_cm, aes(x = Actual, y = Predicted)) +
    geom_tile(aes(fill = Freq), color = 'white') +
    geom_text(aes(label = sprintf("%d", Freq)), vjust = 1) +
    scale_fill_gradient(low = "white", high = "steelblue") +
    theme_minimal() +
    labs(fill = "Frequency", title = paste(model_name, "Confusion Matrix"), x = "Actual outcome", y = "Predicted outcome") +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))
}

cm_logistic <- table(Actual = actual, Predicted = pred.class.logistic)
confusion_matrix_plot(cm_logistic, model_name = "Logistic Regression")

## Classification Tree Model
CART <- rpart(diabetes ~ ., data = train, method = "class")

# Predict on the test set
pred.probabilities.CART <- predict(CART, newdata = test, type = "prob")[, 2]

# Convert probabilities to class labels using a threshold of 0.5
pred.class.CART <- ifelse(pred.probabilities.CART > 0.5, 1, 0)

# Confusion Matrix
cm_CART <- table(Actual = actual, Predicted = pred.class.CART)
confusion_matrix_plot(cm_CART, model_name = "Classification Tree (CART)")

## Lasso Model
x_train <- model.matrix(diabetes ~ ., data = train)[,-1]
y_train <- train$diabetes
x_test <- model.matrix(diabetes ~ ., data = test)[,-1]

# Cross-Validation to find the best lambda
lasso <- glmnet(x_train, y_train, alpha = 1, family = "binomial")
cv.lasso <- cv.glmnet(x_train, y_train, alpha = 1, family = "binomial")
best_lambda <- cv.lasso$lambda.min

# Predict on the test set using the best lambda
pred.probabilities.lasso <- predict(lasso, newx = x_test, type = "response", s = best_lambda)[, 1]

# Convert probabilities to class labels using a threshold of 0.5
pred.class.lasso <- ifelse(pred.probabilities.lasso > 0.5, 1, 0)

# Confusion Matrix
cm_lasso <- table(Actual = actual, Predicted = pred.class.lasso)
confusion_matrix_plot(cm_lasso, model_name = "Lasso Regression")

# Predict on the test set using the best cross-validated model

# Logistic Regression
pred.probabilities.logistic <- predict(cv_logistic, newdata = test, type = "prob")[, 2]
pred.class.logistic <- ifelse(pred.probabilities.logistic > 0.5, 1, 0)

# CART
pred.probabilities.CART <- predict(cv_CART, newdata = test, type = "prob")[, 2]
pred.class.CART <- ifelse(pred.probabilities.CART > 0.5, 1, 0)

# Lasso Regression
pred.probabilities.lasso <- predict(lasso, newx = x_test, s = best_lambda, type = "response")
pred.class.lasso <- ifelse(pred.probabilities.lasso > 0.5, 1, 0)

# Create confusion matrices
cm_logistic <- table(Actual = test$diabetes, Predicted = pred.class.logistic)
cm_CART <- table(Actual = test$diabetes, Predicted = pred.class.CART)
cm_lasso <- table(Actual = test$diabetes, Predicted = pred.class.lasso)

# Evaluate and print metrics for each model
evaluate_model <- function(cm) {
  accuracy <- sum(diag(cm)) / sum(cm)
  precision <- cm[2, 2] / sum(cm[, 2])
  recall <- cm[2, 2] / sum(cm[2, ])
  f1_score <- 2 * ((precision * recall) / (precision + recall))
  
  return(list(Accuracy = accuracy, Precision = precision, Recall = recall, F1_Score = f1_score))
}

metrics_logistic <- evaluate_model(cm_logistic)
metrics_CART <- evaluate_model(cm_CART)
metrics_lasso <- evaluate_model(cm_lasso)
